<subSubSection pageId="81" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="81.[128,654,941,1352]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">
COMMENTS: The specimen collected on 
<date pageId="81" pageNumber="81" value="1815-07-12">12 July 1815</date>
at Renthendorf was designated the 
<typeStatus box="[128,233,1152,1174]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">lectotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." box="[280,509,1152,1174]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" pagination="4 - 63" refId="ref135665" refString="Hartert, E. 1918 a. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. A. Types in the Brehm Collection. Novitates Zoologicae 25: 4 - 63." type="journal article" year="1918">Hartert (1918a: 26)</bibRefCitation>
, who added that Brehm had described 
<taxonomicName box="[496,575,1181,1204]" class="Aves" family="Sittidae" genus="Sitta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="advena">
<emphasis box="[496,575,1181,1204]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">advena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from ‘‘exceptionally pale, partially juvenile, specimens.’’ No other specimens from Renthendorf that came to AMNH were collected early enough to have been used by Brehm in his description of this form.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
